<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,1520,1700]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
This is still a very poorly known species and differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[829,990,1520,1545]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verticillata">
<emphasis box="[829,990,1520,1545]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. verticillata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
essentially in its shaggier pubescence and stiffly erect habit plus its well-developed short shoots (brachyblasts). 
<collectionCode box="[1051,1072,1558,1584]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15406" name="Harvard University - Arnold Arboretum" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="Herbarium">A</collectionCode>
critical revision of herbarium specimens, and preferably field studies are required to clarify the affinities of this taxon. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ricardi" authorityYear="1957" box="[1189,1409,1597,1622]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stitchkinii">
<emphasis box="[1189,1409,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Balbisia stitchkinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically intermediate between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steudel" authorityYear="1840" baseAuthorityName="Lindl." box="[639,836,1636,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Cruckshanksia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="peduncularis">
<emphasis box="[639,836,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. peduncularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reiche" authorityYear="1896" baseAuthorityName="Phil." box="[898,1081,1636,1661]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vivianiaceae" genus="Balbisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphylla">
<emphasis box="[898,1081,1636,1661]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">B. microphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and may represent either an independent, closely allied lineage, or a natural hybrid between the two.
</paragraph>
